5:
That's our target? It's bigger than 
I thought it'd be...
9:
Keep your guard up. He is one of 
a cruel breed of dragons that have 
only a single purpose: to destroy.
13:
Yeah... He's a mean-looking one, all 
right.
16:
What I want to know is... Is he going to 
taste good?
19:
Well, there's a popular saying that 
goes, "The nastier the dragon, the 
sweeter the flesh."
23:
That's good enough for me! Let's beat 
this bad boy!
26:
Hah. You'd jump off a cliff if there was 
a good meal at the bottom of it.
59:
I'm fine! It will take a far stronger blow 
to crush my armor!
77: Azel! The hell were you doing?!
79:
If you hadn't been hoverin' in front of 
Alk, the fight would've been over in two 
blows!
82: I was only trying to keep him safe.
99:
Okay. It HAS to be over this time. 
Right?!
102:
Heh. Not bad.
What'd you think, Azel?
107:
I think Alk... has more than proven his 
strength.
115:
Alk, I owe you an apology. It seems 
that, somewhere along the road, 
I ceased seeing you as a warrior.
118: However... you are not my brother.
122:
Gee, uh, that's a lot less revelatory 
than "I am your father."
125:
W-what I mean to say is, I had lost 
sight of that simple fact...
131:
Yes, a younger one.
One day, he was attacked by a dragon, 
and I... failed to protect him.
133:
You remind me of him. So much so 
that I've begun to confuse the two of 
you.
142:
But you are not my younger brother. 
You are a fellow warriora brother-in-
arms.
Alk, Nimbus... Thank you for opening 
my eyes.
146:
Don't thank me. I only yelled 'cause 
you were starting to piss me off.
149:
...By the way, Alk. I have a request to 
make of a fellow warrior such as 
yourself.
157:
My wounds must be tended to. There is 
a forest ahead of here, from which I'd 
like you to bring back some herbs.
165: Wait. That place is miles away!
168:
The dragon dealt me a fierce blow. If 
I don't get those herbs quickly, I fear 
the wound may turn fatal.
170:
What? What was all that about your 
armor then?!
173:
My armor? I don't recollect saying 
anything about my armor... Please 
hurry, Alk.
178: His life's in your hands, friend.
182:
Once I've been seen to, there's still the 
matter of transporting the carcass. 
You must make haste if we're to return 
to Starview before sundown.
185:
So, Alk? Are we gonna have that 
dragon barbeque tonight or not?
189:
Y-yeah, but... why do I have to do 
everything?!
193:
You are a warrior, Alk. Warriors are 
strong, stoic. They do not grouse.
197:
Yeah. What are you waiting for... 
warrior?
